25 YEARS AGO
the first coast-to-coast
air route was opened
A quarter of a century has gone by since the Post Office Department
pioneered the first coast-to-coast air mail service over the route that
always has been, is now and always will be, the straight, strategic
route across the United States. In years between 1920 and 1945, the
very history of commercial aviation has been written along this very
same route. Two-way radio, stewardess service, full-feathering propel-
lers, multi-motored, all-metal 3-mile-a-minute planes, automatic pilot,
static control, blind landing devices and scores of other aviation im-
provements were born on this mid-continent route, known today as
United's Main Line Airway, serving 53 cities in 17 states, the District
of Columbia and Canada.
